The paper discusses a new attack on the Kirchhoff-law-Johnson-noise (KLJN) secure key exchange system that utilizes cable resistance losses and the lack of exact thermal equilibrium in practical applications. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), computer engineering (cs.CE), electronic engineering (cs.ET), or multimedia (cs.MM). However, since the paper primarily focuses on the security of the KLJN scheme, which is a cryptographic protocol, cs.CR is the most likely category. The other categories are also possible because they involve topics related to the KLJN scheme, such as signal processing and communication systems.
